17 to the direct rollover requirements to the extent permitted by 26 U.S.C. 401(a)(31) and the regu-
18 lations implementing that section.
19 (5) All references in this section to federal laws and regulations are to the laws and regulations
20 in effect on December 31, [2023] 2025.
21 (6) For purposes of this section:
22 (a) “Distributee” means a member, a member’s surviving spouse or a member’s alternate payee
23 under ORS 238.465.
24 (b) “Eligible retirement plan” means:
25 (A) An individual retirement account described in 26 U.S.C. 408(a);
26 (B) An individual retirement annuity described in 26 U.S.C. 408(b), other than an endowment
27 contract;
28 (C) A qualified trust under 26 U.S.C. 401(a), that is a defined contribution or defined benefit plan
29 and permits the acceptance of rollover contributions;
30 (D) An annuity plan described in 26 U.S.C. 403(a);
31 (E) An eligible deferred compensation plan described in 26 U.S.C. 457(b) that is maintained by
32 an eligible governmental employer described in 26 U.S.C. 457(e)(1)(A) and that agrees to account
33 separately for amounts transferred into such plan from the distributing plan; or
34 (F) An annuity contract described in 26 U.S.C. 403(b).
