19 SECTION 36. ORS 314.306 is amended to read:
20 314.306. (1) If a taxpayer excludes an amount from federal gross income by reason of the dis-
21 charge of indebtedness of the taxpayer under section 108(a)(1)(A) of the Internal Revenue Code (re-
22 lating to discharge of indebtedness in a bankruptcy declared under U.S.C. Title 11), then, with
23 respect to that portion of the excluded amount that is apportioned to Oregon, the taxpayer shall
24 apply the rules in 11 U.S.C. 346(j), as amended and in effect on December 31, [2023] 2025.
25 (2) If a taxpayer excludes an amount from federal gross income by reason of the discharge of
26 indebtedness of the taxpayer under section 108(a)(1)(B) or (C) of the Internal Revenue Code (relating
27 to discharge of indebtedness in insolvency or discharge of qualified farm indebtedness), then, with
28 respect to that portion of the excluded amount that is apportioned to Oregon, the following para-
29 graphs shall apply, in the following order:
30 (a) If the taxpayer has made the election under section 108(b)(5) of the Internal Revenue Code
31 to first reduce the basis of the depreciable property of the taxpayer, the election shall also be ef-
32 fective for Oregon tax purposes. A corresponding reduction in the basis of the depreciable property
33 of the taxpayer shall be made for Oregon tax purposes.
34 (b) The amount, if any, by which the following attributes are reduced under section 108(b)(1) of
35 the Internal Revenue Code for federal tax purposes shall be added back for Oregon tax purposes:
36 (A) Federal net operating loss.
37 (B) Capital loss carryover.
38 (C) Basis of the property of the taxpayer, excluding amounts subject to the election under sec-
39 tion 108(b)(5) of the Internal Revenue Code.
40 (D) Passive activity loss carryover.
41 (c) Excluding amounts subject to the election in section 108(b)(5) of the Internal Revenue Code:
42 (A) Any Oregon net operating loss of an individual or corporate taxpayer, including a net op-
43 erating loss carryover to the taxpayer, shall be reduced by the amount of discharged indebtedness.
44 (B) Any net capital loss for the taxable year of the discharge, and any capital loss carryover to
45 the taxable year, shall be reduced by the amount of discharged indebtedness minus the total amount
[21]

A-Eng. SB 1507
1 taken into account under subparagraph (A) of this paragraph.
2 (C) The basis of the property of the taxpayer shall be reduced by the amount of discharged
3 indebtedness minus the total amount taken into account under subparagraphs (A) and (B) of this
4 paragraph.
5 (D) The passive activity loss carryover under section 469(b) of the Internal Revenue Code from
6 the taxable year of the discharge shall be reduced by the amount of discharged indebtedness minus
7 the total amount taken into account under subparagraphs (A), (B) and (C) of this paragraph.
