1 SECTION 41. ORS 317.010 is amended to read:
2 317.010. As used in this chapter, unless the context requires otherwise:
3 (1) “Centrally assessed corporation” means every corporation the property of which is assessed
4 by the Department of Revenue under ORS 308.505 to 308.674.
5 (2) “Department” means the Department of Revenue.
6 (3)(a) “Consolidated federal return” means the return permitted or required to be filed by a
7 group of affiliated corporations under section 1501 of the Internal Revenue Code.
8 (b) “Consolidated state return” means the return required to be filed under ORS 317.710 (5).
9 (4) “Doing business” means any transaction or transactions in the course of its activities con-
10 ducted within the state by a national banking association, or any other corporation; provided, how-
11 ever, that a foreign corporation whose activities in this state are confined to purchases of personal
12 property, and the storage thereof incident to shipment outside the state, shall not be deemed to be
13 doing business unless such foreign corporation is an affiliate of another foreign or domestic corpo-
14 ration which is doing business in Oregon. Whether or not corporations are affiliated shall be de-
15 termined as provided in section 1504 of the Internal Revenue Code.
16 (5) “Excise tax” means a tax measured by or according to net income imposed upon national
